Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Without peeling, chop the @red potato{1} into 2cm cubes. Finely chop the @rosemary{2}(leaves only) and the @walnuts{3}.

Toss the potatoes in a good splash of @olive oil{}, half of the rosemary and a good grind of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on a #baking tray{} and bake in the oven for ~{25-30%minutes} until crunchy and delicious.

Place your hand flat on top of each @British chicken breasts{2} and slice through the middle so it opens like a book.

> This is called 'butterflying' and speeds up the cooking time.

Coat each chicken breast in 1 tsp of @olive oil{}.

Combine the @panko breadcrumbs{3}, walnuts, remaining rosemary and a good pinch of salt and pepper in a #shallow dish{}. Spoon the herby mixture on top of each chicken breast and push it onto the meat.

Put the chicken in your oven and bake for ~{15-20%minutes} until the chicken is cooked through (i.e. it is no longer pink in the middle) and the breadcrumbs have become golden-brown and crispy.

> Once cooked, turn your grill to medium-high and grill the top for a further minute to make it extra crunchy.

Drizzle the @balsamic vinegar{1} and a bit of olive oil over the @lambs lettuce and bulls blood leaves{1} and gently toss. Serve your chicken with your crispy potatoes and salad leaves on the side.

